{
  "texts": [
    "Both are evaluative measures of individuals' achievements, typically quantified.",
    "Furthermore, the social relationships underpinning these evaluations are akin.",
    "Performance appraisal hinges on superior-subordinate dynamics, paralleling the teacherstudent relationship in Chinese academic appraisal.",
    "Lastly, both employees and students exhibit significant concern regarding evaluation fairness.",
    "It is therefore justified to transpose organizational justice theory to educational justice and recast performance appraisal as academic assessment."
  ]
}